employee who is required by the regulations under this chapter to be trained
and certified in first aid, and consequently renders first aid care as provided
by this chapter, shall not be liable for any civil damages resulting from the
employee's acts or omissions, except for such damages as may result from the
employee's gross negligence or wanton acts or omissions. [L 1976, c 155, ยง1;
